Implemented AVBOIT for alpha/transparent mesh rendering, using the SIGGRAPH 2025 AVBOIT deck as the algorithm reference: https://advances.realtimerendering.com/s2025/content/AVBOIT_SIG2025_MDROBOT-final.pdf

What changed:
- Added AVBOIT frame targets, buffers, binding sets, pass selection, and transparent material detection in [renderer_system.h](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/impl/ecs_graphics/renderer_system.h) and [renderer_system.cpp](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/impl/ecs_graphics/renderer_system.cpp).
- Added the AVBOIT pass sequence: low-res occupancy, 1D depth-warp LUT generation, low-res extinction splat, transmittance integration, full-res additive transparent accumulation, then composite.
- Added built-in AVBOIT shader assets under `/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/impl/assets/graphics/avboit_*`.
- Updated [deferred_composite_ps.glsl](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/impl/assets/graphics/deferred_composite_ps.glsl) to composite transparent AVBOIT accumulation over the deferred opaque result.
- Fixed Vulkan meshlet pipeline state in [vulkan_meshlets.cpp](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/core/graphics/vulkan/vulkan_meshlets.cpp) so meshlet pipelines honor render-state depth compare and blend attachments. AVBOIT accumulation depends on this being real, not hardcoded.

Transparent materials opt in with material parameters like `alpha`/`opacity` below `1.0`, or `render_mode`, `alpha_mode`, or `transparency` set to values like `transparent`, `translucent`, `blend`, or `avboit`.

One important contract: transparent AVBOIT passes use the material mesh shader for geometry/color generation, then engine AVBOIT pixel shaders for occupancy/extinction/accumulation. So transparent color currently comes from mesh-generated `outColor` plus material `alpha`/`opacity`; arbitrary material pixel shader shading is still used for opaque, not invoked inside the AVBOIT passes.

